node.text: I have been working on the best way to teach skateboarding online for a long time.  Not just videos but also follow up and help along the way.  This has been in the works for over 10 years and everything that we do at Braille all leads up to this.  Interesting a new person in skateboarding, getting them started skateboarding, teaching them their very first tricks, progressing from there, and hopefully they get so stoked that they then turn around and help other learn.  Skateboarding for 27 years I have learned a lot and the Braille Army plus membership is my way of sharing what I have learned through courses, as well as the best way to achieve that whole process described above.  When I say the purpose is to push skateboarding all over the world thats not a tag line or a marketing campaign I am very serious about that goal.  I put the map of the world there so we could literally track the expansion of skateboarding as new people pick up a board and take their first push.  Thank you for being a part of this journey I love every single one of you and together lets build an awesome community of skaters!  I will likely be talking a lot more about this and giving updates as we roll forward.  If you have any questions please ask me.  Your help and support spreading skateboarding is what will make all the difference and I am here to help you be the best skater you can be.  Link in bio to join the crusade on Braille Army +. @brailleskate #pushskateboarding #skateboarding #skateboard #skateboardingisfun #brailleskateboarding
